  "prompt": "How easy is it to submit a question on Quora?",
  "response": "Submitting a question on Quora is **very easy**. Here's a breakdown of the process and why it's so simple:\n\n*   **Clear Input Field:** Quora has a prominent search bar/question input field at the top of almost every page. It usually says something like \"What do you want to ask or share?\" or \"Ask a question\". It's hard to miss.\n\n*   **Simple Text Entry:** You just type your question directly into the input field.\n\n*   **Suggestions & Auto-Completion:** As you type, Quora often suggests related questions that already exist. This helps prevent duplicates.\n\n*   **Formatting Options:** While the primary focus is on the text of the question, you might have some basic formatting options (like bolding, italics) available when writing a description.\n\n*   **Topic Selection:** After typing your question, Quora will prompt you to add relevant topics. This helps route your question to the right audience. The system might even suggest topics based on the text of your question.\n\n*   **Optional Description (Details):** You can add more details in a separate description field to clarify your question and give context. This is optional but often recommended.\n\n*   **One-Click Submission:** Finally, you just click a \"Post\" or \"Ask\" button to submit your question.\n\n**In short, the process is designed to be quick and intuitive. You can usually ask a question in under a minute.**\n\n**However, keep these points in mind for better question-asking:**\n\n*   **Clarity is Key:** While it's easy to submit, spending time crafting a clear, concise, and well-written question will greatly improve the quality of the answers you receive.\n*   **Search First:** Before asking, take a few moments to search Quora to see if a similar question has already been answered.\n*   **Add Details:** Provide enough context so that people understand what you're asking. Avoid overly broad or vague questions.\n*   **Choose Relevant Topics:** Selecting the right topics is crucial for getting your question seen by the right people.\n\nSo, while the *mechanics* of submitting a question are incredibly easy, the *art* of asking a *good* question that gets helpful answers takes a little more effort.\n",
